\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces The achievable region $\setbox \z@ \hbox {\mathsurround \z@ $\textstyle A$}\mathaccent "0365{A}_{2}$ on the $(H, \varepsilon )$ plane. Upper boundary $\varepsilon = H/2$ (Hellman--Raviv, tight via $\Pi _{\alpha }^{\mathrm  {HR}}$). Lower boundary $\varepsilon = H_{\mathrm  {bin}}^{-1}(H)$ (Fano, tight via $\Pi _{\varepsilon }^{\mathrm  {F}}$). Maximum width $w^{*} \approx 0.1610$ attained at $\varepsilon = 1/5$. Every $(\varepsilon ^{\!*}_{\Pi }, H(f \mid \Pi ))$ from a finite partition and binary label lies in the shaded region; both boundaries and the interior are achievable.}}{7}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
